Depends. 170 workload depends on the individual a lot. 168 is pretty light, but I have no idea about 152.

152 is fine. I spent on average 6-8 hrs on biweekly(or every three weeks) problem set. The lab and lab report took me more and most of my time.

---------------

Personally I found 152 to be about as much work as 170. I took it with Prof. Wawrzynek in Fall 2016, and there was talk that the course may be redesigned next time it is taught, so be aware of that. 168 was about half the workload as 170.
